[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    151[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   1. **Mental-health records are additionally protected beyond HIPAA baseline in many states.** California's CMIA, New York's mental-hygiene law, Illinois's Mental Health and Developmental Disabilities Confidentiality Act, Massachusetts's mental-health-privacy provisions, and similar statutes in other states impose enhanced confidentiality requirements, restrict disclosure even with patient consent in some circumstances, and may impose specific retention and access-control requirements distinct from general medical records. Psychotherapy notes have additional HIPAA Privacy Rule protections. The architecture should specify the per-state mental-health-record retention floor reconciliation and the per-record-class retention regime distinct from the audit-archive.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    152[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    153[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   2. **Substance-use treatment data is governed by 42 CFR Part 2 with specific consent and disclosure restrictions.** Disclosures of substance-use treatment information have stricter consent requirements than HIPAA, with specific re-disclosure restrictions and audit obligations. The architecture should specify the 42 CFR Part 2 handling for substance-use-related conversation content with separate consent, separate access-control, and separate disclosure-tracking.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    154[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    155[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   3. **The sensitive-disclosure store is recipe-acute as the recipe's load-bearing additionally-protected-PHI artifact.** Disclosures of intimate-partner violence, child abuse, elder abuse, substance-use crisis, eating-disorder behavior, severe medication side effects, medication-discontinuation, and trauma disclosures are statutorily protected with additional layers of access control. The architecture should specify the sensitive-disclosure store's archive-reference discipline (the working store carries minimal-context excerpts; the archive carries the full disclosure with separately-keyed KMS), the per-disclosure-class access-control surface (mental-health-licensed-clinician access only for some categories; mandatory-reporter-credentialed-clinician access only for mandatory-reporting-relevant categories), and the per-disclosure-class retention regime.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    156[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    157[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   4. **The crisis-event record is recipe-acute as the recipe's load-bearing life-safety-critical record.** Crisis events are the highest-stakes records the bot ever produces (the bot's failure on a crisis screen is foreseeably life-or-death; the bot's correct handling of a crisis is the institutional-malpractice-defense artifact). The architecture should specify the crisis-event record's archive-reference discipline, the per-crisis-event-class access-control surface (clinical-leadership and post-market-surveillance and incident-review access), and the per-crisis-event retention regime sized to the longest of HIPAA, state mental-health, FDA SaMD, and litigation-hold floors.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    158[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    159[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   5. **The support-decision-record journal accumulates over multi-year support relationships with mental-health-PHI-rich content.** The decision_record's decision_payload (therapeutic_content_delivered, safety_plan_step_surfaced, symptom_log_recorded, crisis_pathway_engaged, warm_handoff_initiated, mandatory_report_routed, psychoeducation_delivered, sensitive_disclosure_recorded) and citations are clinically-significant elements with their own retention and access-control profiles distinct from general medical records.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    161[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   6. **The longitudinal store accumulates conversation history, symptom tracking, safety-plan references, sensitive-disclosure flags, and crisis-history flags over multi-year support relationships.** The architecture should specify the per-state mental-health-record retention floor and the per-record-class retention regime distinct from the audit-archive. Pediatric mental-health records (in deployments that serve any minors) often must be retained until age of majority plus the state's adult retention period producing 25+ year retention windows.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    162[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    163[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   7. **The working-store-vs-archive-store discipline is not specified.** Steps 1C, 2H, 3A, 5 (Persist), and 4 audit_tool_call paths embed full content. The architecture should specify the working-store-vs-archive-store split with structural references on the hot path; full content routes to a per-patient archive surface with appropriate KMS key class.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    164[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    165[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   8. **The patient's right to access their longitudinal record per HIPAA and (per state and contract) the right to request deletion is not architecturally elevated.** State mental-health laws often have specific access-and-deletion provisions distinct from general HIPAA right-of-access. Some states require enhanced patient consent for re-disclosure to subsequent providers. The architecture should specify the patient-right-of-access workflow and the state-and-contract-permitted deletion workflow with deletion-vs-retention-conflict resolution (FDA SaMD post-market obligations and certain state mental-health statutes may prohibit deletion of certain record classes).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    166[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    167[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   9. **The per-record-class access-control surface is not specified.** The audit pipeline's access-control surface is the audit-and-compliance team plus the privacy officer. The longitudinal-store's access-control surface is the patient (through the institution's patient-record-access pathway per HIPAA and state mental-health-record statutes) plus, with consent, the patient's care team. The support-decision-record-journal's access-control surface is the behavioral-health clinical leadership plus compliance plus the audit-and-compliance team plus the data-science team for outcome-correlation. The sensitive-disclosure store's access-control surface is highly restricted to mental-health-licensed-clinician access for some categories and mandatory-reporter-credentialed-clinician access for others. The crisis-event record's access-control surface is clinical-leadership plus post-market-surveillance plus incident-review. Each record class has different access-control needs.
